latestPosts.caption:
💜 EYESHADOW SWATCHES 💜 

✨ Dede Signature Drops of fantasy eyeshadow palette* 

The way I gasped when I opened this palette for the first time - it's like a colorful party! It has neons, it has deepening shades, it has holos and shifty shimmers. I feel super inspired just by looking at this palette! 🥰

The palette contains 15 shades in total - 10 pigmented mattes and 5 stunning shimmers. I would say that 1 of the shimmers is a multichrome holochrome and the rest are duochromes.

The packaging is sleek, fun and playful. I love the little details like the holographic brand logo inside the mirror and the holographic frames around the eyeshadow pans. The matte eyeshadows has a cute imprint too, which makes it look even more professional. The eyeshadow pans are magnetic. Another thing that I appreciate is that the shimmer eyeshadows are covered with a protecting plastic piece to prevent them from breaking during delivery. 

I was surprised by how well the neon shadows showed up on the skin because those are normally really tricky to formulate. I find that the matte formula is on par with the Fearless Holiday palette, which I happen to really love. There is a couple of different shimmer formulas, some are flakier and some are very smooth. But as long as you're using a glitter glue with it, they will apply nicely on the lids. 

There will also be launching 6 cute lip kits in this collection. I have 3 of them that I will show you soon, so stay tuned for that! 

For my fellow EU friends, this palette will launch on Monolith Shop EU during their next launch. I don't think that the lip kits will be included, but I will of course look it up. 

* = Gifted.

latestPosts.caption:
💜 EYESHADOW SWATCHES 💜 

✨ Titanium Foxes Cosmetics Hidden Peace eyeshadow palette*

Every time Titanium Foxes Cosmetics releases something new, I can always trust that it's going to be good. And there is no exception with the Hidden Peace palette. I can already now predict that this will be one of my top favourite palettes from the brand because it has a little bit of everything that I like in a colour story. Contrast, sparkle, murky greens, some neutrals, some colorful deeper mattes... I could probably go on all day, but I probably don't need to convince you why this is a great colour story.

I really like the theme of this palette and the colour story is very peaceful to me. 

The quality is on par with the other palettes that I own from the brand. The mattes are pigmented and very easy to blend and the shimmers are creamy and reflective. Due to the creamy quality of the shimmers, I can imagine that they might crease on oily lids - but that's just a speculation since I don't have this issue myself.

Did you pick up this palette? 👀

* = Gifted for paid swatches with no obligation to post.

latestPosts.caption:
💜 EYESHADOW SWATCHES 💜 

✨ Glaminatrix Cosmetics Nearly Natural eyeshadow palette 

If it's something that Glaminatrix Cosmetics is good at, it's creating interesting neutral palettes. This palette is a revamped version of the Nearly Natural palette, but I never owned that palette. According to the brand, this version has a upgraded formula and added shades. 

This palette contains 20 colours in total;

9 metallic shimmers 

10 smooth, blendable mattes 

1 brand new baked eyeshadow formula 

The pans are slightly smaller than most other palettes, 22,5 mm. They are also magnetic.

Colour story wise, this is close to my ideal neutral palette because it has a bit of everything. Bold tones, intense shimmers, grungy tones but also a couple of softer tones. Due to the different tones and colour families, I feel like this palette opens up for both glamorous and dramatic looks, but also more softer and sophisticated looks. 

The packaging is sleek and easy to store, which I appreciate. Another detail I love is the cool imprint texture on the surface of the packaging.

I really enjoy the Glaminatrix formula and I find that this palette is on par with the other palettes that I own from the brand.

Did you pick up this palette?
